Day 13:
Step 0: Log in to the Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com/).


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

1. Azure Queue Storage:
Step 1: Create a new Resource Group:

--> Create a Storage Account:
Step 1: You can search STORAGE ACCOUNTS in Search bar.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Storage Accounts name
        b. Performance - Standard
        c. Region
        d. Performance
        e. Access Tier - hot
Step 3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review+create.
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Storage Account.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 2: Click on QUEUE which is located in the overview of Storage Account.
Step 3: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Queue name
Step 4: In Queue, you can add messages, dequeue messages and clear messages.
Step 5: Create 2 LOGIC APPS.

--> Steps to create LOGIC APP:
Step 1:  You can search LOGIC APP in Search bar.
Step 2: Enter the necessary details: 
        a. Logic App name
        b. Subscription
        c. Region
Step 3: Then click on CREATE when you go to review+create.
Step 4: Once depolyment is complete, go to resource group to view your Logic App.
Step 4: Go to Logic App Designer and click on add trigger to add the following in LA1:
      a. HTTP
      b. Azure Queue
Step 5: Repeat the step 4 for LA2 and add what ever trigger you want to.
Step 6: Then for testing click on RUN in Logic App's Overview page.

